// offline_lean_replay is the reserved SAW-side discharge command:
// check a completed Lean proof of the goal and admit the goal only if
// Lean kernel-checks it. It is registered but DISABLED this release —
// it must fail with its named diagnostic and must not solve the goal.
// (Release plan: saw-core-lean/doc/2026-07-14_release-plan.md.)
//
// The goal here is trivially true so that IF replay ever starts
// admitting goals silently, the failure mode this row catches is the
// command succeeding (exit 0) rather than a legitimate proof failure.
prove_print (offline_lean_replay "test.replay_goal") {{ True }};
